```

## Template Placeholders

### Standard Placeholders
| Placeholder | Description | Example |
|-------------|-------------|---------|
| `{ISSUE_KEY}` | Jira issue key | PROJ-123 |
| `{STORY_KEY}` | User story key | PROJ-101 |
| `{EPIC_KEY}` | Epic key | PROJ-100 |
| `{PROJECT_KEY}` | Project key | PROJ |
| `{FEATURE}` | Feature name | Authentication |
| `{TEST_NAME}` | Test name | Verify Valid Credentials |
| `{PRIORITY}` | Priority level | P1, P2, P3, P4 |
| `{AC_REFERENCE}` | AC reference | AC1, AC2 |
| `{JIRA_URL}` | Full Jira URL | https://domain.atlassian.net/browse/PROJ-123 |

### Status Placeholders
| Placeholder | Values |
|-------------|--------|
| `{STATUS}` | To Do, In Progress, Done |
| `{SYNC_STATUS}` | ⏳ Pending, ✅ Synced, ❌ Failed |

## Template Usage

### Creating New Test Case
1. Copy `templates/test-case-template.md`
2. Rename to `[TC] {KEY} - {Feature} - {Name}.md`
3. Replace all placeholders
4. Save in appropriate `test-cases/` folder

### Creating New Test Suite
1. Copy `templates/test-suite-template.md`
2. Rename to `{ISSUE_KEY}.md`
3. Replace all placeholders
4. Save in story folder

## Validation Rules

### Required Fields
- [ ] Issue Key populated
- [ ] Story reference complete
- [ ] At least one test step
- [ ] Expected results for each step
- [ ] Priority assigned
- [ ] Labels assigned

### Format Validation
- Issue keys: `[A-Z]+-\d+` (e.g., PROJ-123)
- Labels: lowercase with hyphens
- Priority: P1, P2, P3, or P4
